### Create Next.js Session Cookie with Recommended Options (TS/JS)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/authentication.mdx

This function `createSession` sets a new session cookie for a given user ID using Next.js's `cookies` API. It includes recommended security options like `httpOnly`, `secure`, and `sameSite` to protect the cookie from client-side access and cross-site requests, and sets an expiration time. This function must be executed on the server.

```ts
import 'server-only'\nimport { cookies } from 'next/headers'\n\nexport async function createSession(userId: string) {\n  const expiresAt = new Date(Date.now() + 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)\n  const session = await encrypt({ userId, expiresAt })\n  const cookieStore = await cookies()\n\n  cookieStore.set('session', session, {\n    httpOnly: true,\n    secure: true,\n    expires: expiresAt,\n    sameSite: 'lax',\n    path: '/',\n  })\n}
```

